OL,3,C'Welfare cheats' campaign temporarily
OL,4,Cweakened belief in support ` study
OL,6,FThe Government's 'welfare cheats'
OL,7,Fcampaign temporarily weakened belief
OL,8,Fin Ireland that social benefits help
OL,9,Fprevent poverty, according to a study.
OL,11,FThe research by the Esri (Economic and
OL,12,FSocial Research Institute), carried
OL,13,Fout in partnership with Community
OL,14,FFoundation Ireland, found that while
OL,15,F64% of the population believe that
OL,16,F'social benefits help prevent
OL,17,Fpoverty', this view was temporarily
OL,18,Fweakened after the launch of the
OL,19,Fgovernment's 'welfare cheats cheat us
OL,20,Fall' campaign on welfare fraud in 2017.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/11
