OL,6,FIt found that 76% of respondents in
OL,7,FIreland indicated that they either
OL,8,F'agree' (45%) or 'agree strongly'
OL,9,F(31%) that the Government should
OL,10,Freduce income differences.
OL,12,FThis percentage is higher than the
OL,13,FEuropean average of 71% and in other
OL,14,FEuropean countries such as the UK
OL,15,F(70%) and Germany (68%).
OL,17,FThe research found that wanting to
OL,18,Freduce income inequality is stronger
OL,19,Famong women, young people and the
OL,20,Fworking class.
