OL,6,FWhile a high proportion of respondents
OL,7,Fin Ireland (64%) believe that social
OL,8,Fbenefits prevent poverty (down
OL,9,Fslightly from 69% in 2009), there are
OL,10,Falso more negative sentiments, with
OL,11,F58% believing that 'social benefits
OL,12,Fmake people lazy'.
OL,14,FYounger people, those on the right of
OL,15,Fthe left-right scale, and those with
OL,16,Flower educational attainment are more
OL,17,Flikely to agree that social benefits
OL,18,Fmake people lazy.
